text: Dondukovskaya () is a rural locality (a stanitsa) and the administrative center of Dondukovskoye Rural Settlement of Giaginsky District, Adygea, Russia. The population was 6636 as of 2018. There are 56 streets.Улицы станицы Дондуковская == Geography == The stanitsa is located 21 km east from Giaginskaya in the steppe zone on the Fars River. == Ethnicity == The stanitsa is inhabited by Russians, Armenians, Ukrainians, Adygheans. == References == Category:Rural localities in Giaginsky District
title: Dondukovskaya
